===Etymology 1===
The sense of "safeguard" comes from {{L.}} {{term|Palladium|lang=la}} (the image of {{term|Pallas}} that protected {{term|Troy}}), from {{Gr.}} {{term|sc=Grek|Παλλάδιον|lang=el}}, from {{term|sc=Grek|Πάλλας|lang=el}}, an alternative name for {{term|Athena}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|pl=palladia}}

# A safeguard {{i|from a statue of Athena that was believed to safeguard the ancient city of Troy}}.

